<b>Diet in Autism</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">On account of their condition, children with autism could have erratic eating patterns and habits that could lead to deficiencies. Also, studies have shown that some foods must be avoided as they seem to aggravate the behavior of the brain which in turn have a negative effect. Some of the foods to be avoided include casein (from dairy products), gluten, corn, sugar, additives, preservatives, dyes and all artificial colors, flavorings and sweeteners.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Traditional western methods are widely used for treating Autism, Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, ‚Äúillness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.‚Äù¬†</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of Autism is: </span><b>Distrust the natural flow and process of life.¬†</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of doing this is through saying or writing affirmations.¬†</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing Autism is: </span><b>I love and approve of myself and I trust in the process of life. I am safe</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.¬†</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"0";}}